The paper deals with regular operations on languages represented by automata, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The study of complexity of these operations involves analyzing the structure of the automata, which can be seen as a data structure (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the number of states required to represent the languages, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of regular languages and automata is closely related to logic and algebra, which are covered under the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and information theory (cs.IT).
